MORE government employees have been arrested for fraud and corruption in KZN.The employees are supposed to protect the public and offer their services for free, but they have been demanding bribes.To show that no one is above the law, the Hawks arrested two senior government employees this week.Hawks spokesman Captain Simphiwe Mhlongo said their Durban commercial crime unit arrested a 33-year-old Home Affairs manager for fraud on Wednesday. He was bust with his accomplice (31).&ldquo;The two officials are suspected of helping a foreigner obtain a fraudulent South African passport. They appeared in the Durban Specialised Commercial Crime Court on Wednesday and were granted bail of R1 500 each. The case was postponed to 20 January,&rdquo; said Mhlongo.In another bust, cops from the Hawks&rsquo; serious corruption investigations unit arrested a 40-year-old public prosecutor at the Ixopo Magistrates Court for corruption on Monday. &ldquo;Our members had received information that the prosecutor demanded money from a complainant in order not to charge him for stock theft,&rdquo; Mhlongo said.An undercover operation was conducted and the prosecutor was caught red-handed while accepting cash. He was arrested inside the court premises. He appeared in the Durban Specialised Commercial Court on Tuesday and was also granted R1 000 bail.